<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900521-0116</DOCNO><DOCID>900521-0116.</DOCID><HL>   Philadelphia Electric   Appeals Rate Decision   By Utility Commission</HL><DATE>05/21/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A7C</SO><CO>   PE</CO><IN>ELECTRIC UTILITIES (ELC)</IN><LP>   PHILADELPHIA -- Philadelphia Electric Co. appealed anApril 19 decision by the Pennsylvania Public UtilityCommission that granted the utility only $242.2 million ofthe $548.6 million rate increase it requested.   Philadelphia Electric said that by denying the raterequest, the commission unconstitutionally deniedshareholders any return on their investment in Limerick No. 2nuclear power station. In denying most of the rate increase,the commission disallowed the company's request to recoverthe costs of building and operating the plant.</LP><TEXT>   In the appeal, filed with the Commonwealth Court ofPennsylvania, Philadelphia Electric alleged that thecommission approved various aspects of the project in themid-1980s, and then &quot;suddenly reversed course&quot; this year.</TEXT></DOC>